### 2. **VC-Claude-Code-Prompts.md** (40 pages, Your Build Guide)
**Purpose**: 16 focused prompts for Claude Code sessions covering every technical aspect of VolunteerCalendar.

**Prompts** (use 2–3/week, weeks 2–9):
1. Full-stack architecture & tech stack validation
2. PostgreSQL database schema & data modeling
3. Planning Center API integration pattern
4. Core scheduling algorithm (fair rotations + conflict detection)
5. Authentication & multi-tenant isolation
6. Draft→Approve→Publish workflow state machine
7. Email & SMS templating + delivery
8. Volunteer response flow & real-time dashboard
9. Error handling & logging strategy
10. Testing strategy (unit, integration, E2E)
11. Monitoring, observability & uptime
12. Scalability & performance optimization
13. Security & data privacy
14. Billing & subscription management
15. Analytics & reporting for admins
16. Setup wizard & onboarding flow

**When to use**: Week-by-week technical build guidance. Paste one prompt per Claude Code session, get back detailed analysis, pseudocode, architecture diagrams, implementation guides.

**Key takeaway**: Each prompt is self-contained; you get architecture, code stubs, and next-step guidance in minutes instead of hours of research.

**Expected outputs per session**: 
- Architecture diagrams (ASCII/Mermaid)
- Pseudocode
- SQL/TypeScript stubs
- Error handling patterns
- Testing examples
- Implementation guides

